tip.text: Order the hot sharing platter. All the dishes were delicious but the black cod fillet tasted the best! The portion is perfect for two.

formattedAddress: Four Seasons Resort Bali (Jalan Bukit Permai)

tip.text: The pork rice bowl (野郎燒豬丼) was incredible. So satisfying with every bite! Definitely want to come back and have another serve.

contact.facebookName: 一碗大滿足「燒丼株式會社」

venue.name: 燒丼株式會社 Don Show Buri

tip.text: Have come here a number of times for pizza, pasta & tea and have always been pleasantly surprised. If you order a pot of tea, you'll get a warm muffin and a biscuit too which was a nice surprise!
This place is great, and cheap! 10 dim sum dishes for only $28. Especially enjoyed the chee cheong fun and the fried golden tofu. Will definitely return to try the other dishes we missed.
The 3-cheese penne gratin (aka mac n' cheese) is seriously incredible. Nothing to fault, it tasted super delicious!
Believe me, 533 steps is a lot! It won't be an easy climb to the top and your legs will really hurt, but it'll be worth it to see the view.
Lovely place to sit for lunch and/or a coffee. Nice relaxed vibe inside. I ordered the pea stew with smoked sausage and it was really delicious. Exactly what I needed on a cold, rainy day!

Best art museum experience I've ever had. Even if art isn't your thing, it's still worth paying the entrance to walk through the space and take in the beautiful architecture designed by Peter Zumthor.
This place deserves a better rating. We ordered the steak and ribs & both were great. There is however a really long wait time for food, so don't come here for a quick lunch.
Great staff and fun vibe at night. Ordered the nachos and the open prawn sandwich. Yummy!
Great place for a coffee break amongst the chaos of the mall. Watch out for the seats under the trees, it appears that birds like to visit the cafe and leave their mark on the seats.
Have the räksmörgås. So good and I left very satisfied!
Start your day on a good note by having breakfast here. The coffee is really great and the cinnamon roll was delish!
Try the potato pancakes with whitefish roe. Really delicious. Just wish they had a main course size for this dish!
Incredible food. Great vibe. Love the seats around the counter. Ordered the crayfish toast, meatballs and salmon. All were amazing! Definitely worth spending your $$ here!
Incredible food here at Cuca. Very modern and experimental but super delicious! Order the chef tasting meal and be blown away. Favourite dish was definitely the smoked butterfish!
High tea was perfect here. Love the lunch time slot over the weekend & how they change menu every month. They were very kind to give us a complimentary cake as we were celebrating a birthday!

formattedAddress: #B1-46/47 Raffles City Shopping Centre (252 North Bridge Road)

tip.text: Quaint cafe not far from Novena MRT. Don't be put off by the cluttered interior, food & coffee was delicious. Try the English Waffles. Very yummy!
Try the crustacean bowl. Simply delicious!! The spicy roasted garlic lobster roll is really tasty too. It may look small when it first arrives at your table, but its very filling!
Ordered the rosti with cheese sausage. Very delicious! As good as the famous rosti at Marche.

Decent coffee but severely disappointed by the portion size of the fries. For $11.50, I expected more than just 10 pieces of potatoes. Price needs to be amended to suit because currently its a ripoff!

tip.text: Despite what some people have said, the service here was great! The food was incredibly delicious and everything was very well seasoned. Will definitely be back!

formattedAddress: #02-28, The Star Vista (1 Vista Exchange Green)
#02-28, The Star Vista (1 Vista Exchange Green)

tip.text: There is quite a long wait for food so if you're desperately hungry, you might want to eat elsewhere. It is however, worth the wait as the food is always delicious! Love the perfectly cooked salmon.

Had a nice meal here and the staff were very pleasant to us. The BBQ pork bun was as good as I hoped it to be! Also ordered the pork dumpling with shrimp and carrot cake which were both great as well!
